cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL

This paper is primarily focused on deep convolutional neural networks and their training procedures, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image classification. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the challenges of training deep networks and proposes a new training procedure, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses stochasticity in its approach, which is a common technique in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also evaluates its approach on various datasets, which is relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
